2023/06/26 20:26:42 - Element found with locator: job-details and  locatorType: id

2023/06/26 20:26:42 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:26:42 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:27:16 - Element found with locator: job-details and  locatorType: id

2023/06/26 20:27:16 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:27:16 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:28:02 - Element found with locator: job-details and  locatorType: id

2023/06/26 20:28:02 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:28:02 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:28:24 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:28:24 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:28:44 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:29:01 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:29:01 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

2023/06/26 20:29:15 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:29:15 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:29:59 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:29:59 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:30:35 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:30:35 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

A Keyrus acredita na diversidade e na inclusão. Encorajamos a todos a participarem em nosso processo de contratação, não importando o gênero, idade, raça, religião. Não permitimos nenhum tipo de discriminação. Isto é reforçado no processo de contratação e vivido dessa forma na empresa.

Papéis e Responsabilidades

Estabelecer e conscientizar a organização sobre as políticas de dados Mapear e Catalogar os ativos de dados mapeando o ciclo de vida dos dados. Desenhar dashboards para acompanhamento da qualidade de dados.

Qualificações Essenciais

Experiência em programas de Governança de Dados, especialista em projetos de Dados Mestres -MDM, orquestração de times técnicos e negócio, conhecimentos de modelagem de Dados conceitual e logica, Desenvolvimento de documentações e processos (BPMN) (gestão metadados, políticas, regras de qualidade) com forte atenção a detalhes Experiência com metodologia gestão ágil Conhecimentos LGPD, DAMA DMBOK, Vivencia com ferramentas de catálogo de dados , data quality e MDM.

Nossa missão é Auxiliar as empresas a extrair todo o potencial de Dados e Digital objetivando aumentar seu desempenho, ajudando na transformação, gerando novas alavancas de crescimento e competitividade.

Vem fazer parte do Time Keyrus!

2023/06/26 20:31:46 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Sobre o Picpay

Com mais de dez anos de história, o PicPay é uma empresa de tecnologia que oferece um portfólio completo de serviços financeiros para facilitar a relação com dinheiro e ser a principal conta do dia a dia de milhares de pessoas e empresas.

Atuamos em cinco frentes de negócios: Serviços Financeiros para Pessoa Física, Serviços Financeiros para Pessoa Jurídica, Marketplace Financeiro, PicPay Store, Cripto/Web3 e Investimentos. Fundada em Vitória (ES), a empresa tem mais de 30 milhões de usuários ativos e faz parte do grupo J&F, um dos maiores conglomerados empresariais do Brasil.

Nossa cultura é nosso alicerce e nossa força. Conheça nossos valores: Atitude de Dono(a), Disciplina, Determinação, Disponibilidade, Simplicidade, Humildade e Franqueza.

O respeito, a ética e a busca pela equidade são elementos inegociáveis e fazem parte da prática no nosso dia a dia aqui no PicPay. Por isso, esta vaga está aberta para todas as pessoas, independente de gênero, religião, etnia, deficiência, idade, orientação sexual ou qualquer outro fator.

Responsabilidades e atribuições

Análises exploratórias;
Dashboards para Guided Analytics;
Ponto de contato (BP) dos times de negócio;
Identificação de oportunidade de projetos;
Extração de dados;
Modelagem de dados;

Requisitos e qualificações

SQL / PySpark | Porque dado em planilha é coisa do passado;
Python ou R | Pra quando a coisa fica bem séria;
Looker, Metabase ou outras plataformas de Self-Service de dados | Pra se colocar sempre no lugar do cliente;
Tableau, PowerBi ou outras ferramentas de Data;
Visualization Storytelling | Ninguém aguenta mais tabelão e flat file;
Priorização de demandas e comunicação efetiva com diversos stakeholders.

O que oferecemos

Saúde e Bem-estar: Além de Assistência Médica e Odontológica, oferecemos Seguro de Vida e o Lado a Lado, um programa que cuida de você e seus familiares, com apoio jurídico, social, psicológico e financeiro;

E claro, não podemos esquecer da nossa parceria com a Gympass;

Alimentação/ Mobilidade ou Teletrabalho: Por meio de um cartão de crédito, com ampla aceitação, você recebe seu saldo de Alimentação/Refeição e Mobilidade ou Teletrabalho (de acordo com o seu contrato de trabalho);

Licença Paternidade e Maternidade: Sabemos que esse é um momento especial para uma família, e por isso oferecemos Licença Maternidade estendida de 6 meses, e de Paternidade também estendida de 20 dias. Além disso, nossas mamães PicPay Lovers são acompanhadas pelo programa "Novo Ser", durante toda a gestação e no retorno da licença. Falando nisso, ao retornar da licença maternidade, as mamães ainda contam com a ajuda do Auxílio Creche e também os papais que possuem guarda unilateral ou compartilhada;

Reconhecemos resultados: PPR - Participação nos Resultados do PicPay.

#VemserPicpayLover #Picpay'

Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:32:08 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Job Description

Somos uma empresa de tecnologia movida por nossa paixão por animais de estimação! 💜

Nosso trabalho diário é tornar a vida dos pais dos animais de estimação mais fácil por meio de uma experiência única de aprender, fazer compras e consumir o que eles precisam, a qualquer hora. Sempre centrado no que é melhor para a felicidade e saúde dos animais de estimação.

A Petlove já é a maior empresa de tecnologia na indústria pet do Brasil. Recentemente, adicionamos ao nosso portfólio empresas estratégicas como DogHero, VetSmart, Vetus e Porto.pet para animais de estimação, a fim de perseguir nossa visão de criar o maior ecossistema de animais de estimação do Brasil.

Temos muito orgulho de já ter atendido mais de 5 milhões de clientes em todo o país, mas ainda estamos famintos pelo que vem por aí (o Brasil tem mais de 48 milhões de domicílios com animais de estimação). Se você está procurando uma oportunidade única na vida, adora tecnologia e é realmente apaixonado por animais de estimação, somos perfeitos um para o outro!

O time de Customer Insights é um braço estratégico da área de Customer Experience aqui na Petlove, gerando dados para melhoria de produtos, processos, jornada do cliente, atendimento e eficiência operacional.

Responsibilities and assignments

Como Analista de Inteligência, a pessoa trabalhará no SQUAD de Dados dentro do time de CX, tendo um papel de parceiro de negócios entre as áreas de atendimento (B2B, B2C e Ecossistema) e o time de dados (Shared Services). Atuará como guardião dos OKRS, projetos de grande impacto, envolvendo dados estratégicos, táticos e operacionais de CX, expondo esses dados em relatórios e dashboards no Power BI. Também será responsável pela validação dos dados dispostos, estudos e análises para tomada de decisão.

Requirements And Qualifications

Habilidades que o cargo precisa

Gerenciamento de Stakeholders;
Noções de usabilidade do Google Sheets, Slides e Docs;
Se baseia em fatos e dados para criar soluções;
Conhecimento em SQL, Power BI e Data Studio;
Saber de indicadores de atendimento e CX ( FCR, TMA, TMT, TME, abandono, produtividade, aderência, CSAT, NPS, Churn, LTV entre outros);
Familiaridade com ferramentas de atendimento de chat/voz (Zendesk, Five9, Zenvia, Totalvoice, Atende Simples, Hi Plataform, entre outros).
Disponibilidade para atuar presencialmente 2x na semana

Additional information

Quem somos

Somos uma empresa de tecnologia com mais de 30 anos de mercado, que tem o objetivo de democratizar e simplificar o cuidado com o pet, oferecendo a melhor experiência para tutores e empoderando médicos-veterinários e empreendedores do segmento.

Considerado o maior ecossistema pet do Brasil, o grupo Petlove conta com mais de 15 mil produtos no site e app, serviços DogHero de hospedagem, pet sitter, creche e outros, planos de saúde para cães e gatos, em parceria com a Porto Seguro, e muito mais.

A Petlove é digital, mas também marcamos presença com as nossas lojas físicas em São Paulo (e em breve em outros estados), que além de petshop, oferecem banho e tosa, atendimento veterinário e espaço Pet Play.

Onde tem pet, tem love. Por isso, a Petlove acredita no poder de transformar o mundo em um lugar onde todos os pets possam ser mais felizes e saudáveis.

Nosso jeito de trabalhar

Na Petlove nós somos apaixonados por pets e por pessoas. Por isso, buscamos garantir que somos inclusivos e formamos times diversos, sempre procurando refletir em nossas decisões nosso compromisso com esse tema! Consideramos enriquecedor contratar pessoas com deficiência, de gêneros e orientação sexual diversas, incluindo todas as etnias e religiões, além de todas as idades e demais marcadores de identidade. Temos certeza que só assim formaremos times inconformados, ágeis e comprometidos com o nosso propósito.

Por que você vai amar ser um Petlover?

Muitos benefícios ❤️

Plano de saúde e plano odontológico Porto Seguro para titular e dependentes (sem desconto)
Seguro de vida até 24x do salário (sem desconto)
Cartão Flash Benefícios para maior flexibilidade de uso: você escolhe se vai usar no mercado ou em restaurantes!
Estamos em formato híbrido: oferecemos auxílio home office para ajudar você com os gastos do dia a dia fora do escritório
Programa Todos Sócios
Licença maternidade de 6 meses
Licença paternidade de 20 dias
PLR - atrelado às metas
Convênio farmácia
Day off de aniversário

Oferecemos duas plataformas de atividades físicas: Total Pass e Gympass

Day off em qualquer dia do mês, para você aproveitar como quiser.

Cuidamos dos seus pets 🐾

Apoiamos a adoção responsável! Oferecemos Licença PETernidade de 2 dias para Petlovers que adotarem um pet
Plano de saúde para seu pet para todos os colaboradores
Descontos em todas as compras de produtos no nosso site e app: 15% e 20% para compradores recorrentes
Crédito de R$ 400 anuais para utilizar na DogHero, podendo escolher entre hospedagem, pet sitter e creche.

Mas afinal, o que é ser Petlover?

Ser Petlover é colocar o bem-estar e a felicidade dos pets como prioridade, sempre.

Ser Petlover é valorizar o risco calculado, fazer o que diz e agir com velocidade.

Ser Petlover é atrair, reter e desenvolver os melhores talentos.

Ser Petlover é experimentar e se esforçar para inovar constantemente.

Ser Petlover é trabalhar colaborativamente para construir nossa visão comum.

Ser Petlover é ser eficiente, ágil e simplificar.

Ser Petlover é valorizar a diversidade e a construção de um ambiente cada vez mais inclusivo.

Se identificou? Então vem pra cá!

2023/06/26 20:32:17 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:32:22 - Element found with locator: job-details and  locatorType: id

2023/06/26 20:32:22 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:32:22 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:32:33 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:32:33 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:32:46 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:32:46 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:32:57 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

Sobre a MSXI

Com aproximadamente 7.000 colaboradores presentes em mais de 80 países em todo o mundo, nossos times proporcionam liderança e expertise na indústria automotiva e suas redes de concessionários nos seguintes produtos:

Warranty & Technical

Retail Performance Management
Customer Engagement
Fleet & Mobility

Construindo confiança desde 1931, nossa reputação comprova que somos o parceiro de aproximadamente todas as marcas de veículos do mercado. Nossos talentosos colaboradores nos ajudam a superar nossas ambiciosas metas ano após ano. Se você se identifica com nosso negócio, dê uma olhada em nossas oportunidades de carreira.

2023/06/26 20:33:56 - Element found with locator: job-details and  locatorType: id

2023/06/26 20:33:56 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:33:56 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

Req ID: 426569

Leading societies to a low carbon future, Alstom develops and markets mobility solutions that provide the sustainable foundations for the future of transportation. Our product portfolio ranges from high-speed trains, metros, monorail, and trams to integrated systems, customised services, infrastructure, signalling and digital mobility solutions. Joining us means joining a caring, responsible, and innovative company where more than 70,000 people lead the way to greener and smarter mobility, worldwide

The Latin America (LAM) Business Intelligence (BI) Key User (KU) is responsible for ensuring all LAM site BI needs and opportunities are identified, prioritized and met, using required standard Americas solutions.

The LAM BI KU supports all LAM Product Lines and sites, with responsibility for dashboard, operations data reporting and other automated data tool needs and solutions for all functions/métiers using GSI and landscape systems + supporting data.

Specific responsibilities of the role:
Identify/assess/prioritize all KPI dashboard, operations data reporting & automated data movement / retrieval / formatting tool needs (gaps and opportunities) for all functions/métiers of all GSI sites. Communicate all needs to AME RBPEs and collaborate with RBPEs to ensure all needs are met.
Collaborate with RBPEs to maximize use of (1) existing solutions and (2) common solutions for all Product Lines and sites
Collaborate with RBPEs to maximize solution value versus cost to provide
Ensure target labor-savings improvements from deployed automated tools are identified when requested and achieved when implemented. Define target # of users for tools and facilitate adoption accordingly.
Ensure all site KPI dashboard, operations data reporting & automated data movement / retrieval / formatting tool needs are met with solutions approved by the BI RBPEs. Ensure every non-standard local tool is specifically approved as such by BI RBPEs before it is developed or used. Ensure with BI RPBEs any existing non-standard local tool is either approved to continue, or agreed for replacement with a standard tool.
Ensure all mandatory standard tools, including the GSI leading indicators KPI tool and monthly GSI steering committee templates, are used by all applicable sites
Lead and/or participate in all required testing of new/enhanced automated tools deployments
Ensure necessary training/documentation is provided to end users to ensure solutions awareness and effective use.
Ensure all proposed improvements or changes to automated tools are communicated to RBPE for evaluation and alignment on plan to address.
Create and track required Fiori BW access requests for end users.
Develop/Maintain/Grow LAM GSI expertise/competencies in use of Business Intelligence and tools
Actively support AME Business Intelligence Key User (KU) / Expert network
Consolidate/prioritize/report open points from all sites; provide/facilitate investigation and technical details; Support problem resolutions and Identify/facilitate needed solution enhancements

Qualifications & Experiences

Mandatories
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Business, Engineering, Science or related field
>4 years of experience in Business Intelligence, supply chain, finance, sourcing or quality
>4 years of experience with ERP systems
Strong understanding of Business Intelligence and related tools
Strong understanding of business operations
Proven leadership and influencing skills
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills; Data-oriented mindset with digitalization focus
Excellent written and verbal communication
Ability to perform in ambiguous & challenging situations, effectively cope with change, meet challenging deadlines on simultaneous projects while effectively managing risk and uncertainty
Ability to work effectively with multiple stakeholders in a matrixed environment
Fluent in English

Desirable
>2 years of experience with ERP system implementations
>2 years of experience as an ERP system Key User
>4 years of rail industry experience

Alstom is the leading company in the mobility sector, solving the most interesting challenges for tomorrow’s mobility. That’s why we value inquisitive and innovative people who are passionate about working together to reinvent mobility, making it smarter and more sustainable. Day after day, we are building an agile, inclusive and responsible culture, where a diverse group of people are offered opportunities to learn, grow and advance in their careers, with options across functions and geographic locations. Are you ready to join a truly international community of great people on a challenging journey with a tangible impact and purpose?

Equal opportunity statement:

Alstom is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating an inclusive working environment where all our employees are encouraged to reach their full potential, and individual differences are valued and respected. All qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, disability status, or any other characteristic protected by local law.

Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:35:09 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Job Description

Criamos ambientes onde todas as pessoas são incluídas, acolhidas e valorizadas. Nos empenhamos em ser uma Globo cada vez mais diversa, em representatividade e pensamento, aprendendo uns com os outros e estimulando a criatividade e inovação.

Responsibilities and assignments

Modelo de trabalho: Híbrido - Rio de Janeiro, RJ ou São Paulo, SP.

Sobre a área:

O que nos move na área de Pesquisa e Conhecimento é gerar, integrar e dar sentido ao conhecimento do consumidor para tomada de decisões de impacto positivo. Temos como desafio prestar serviço de soluções de pesquisas, a todas as áreas da Globo, disponibilizando tanto pesquisas ad-hoc como contínuas, além de entregar metodologias e meios para monitoramento da sociedade, desempenho de audiência, entendimento do consumidor, através de estudos, apresentações e acompanhamentos de mercado com visão multiplataforma.

Como será seu dia a dia:

Responsável por rodar modelagens estatísticas como regressões, análises fatoriais, segmentação, modelos preditivos, mapas perceptuais etc.;
Indicar qual análise estatística melhor atende ao que precisamos responder.

Requirements And Qualifications

Do que você precisa:

Formação Superior em Estatística ou afins;
Vivência com Excel, SPSS, R, softwares de estatística;
Conhecimento e experiência com modelagens estatísticas.

Conhecimentos que te destacam:

Ter trabalhado em institutos de pesquisa;
Experiência com Python;
Vivência em Dataviz para obter insights de storytelling em Data Studio ou Power BI.

Additional information

Por que vir para Globo:

Vem e vamos criar histórias e tecnologias juntos.

Na Globo, o encontro de histórias com tecnologia move um time diverso e apaixonado por inovação.

A gente tem a chance de aproximar os brasileiros, criando novas formas de se conectar com eles.

Aqui, cada um faz a transformação acontecer.

Nossos processos seletivos estão acontecendo de forma 100% remota e nós encorajamos inscrições de qualquer lugar do Brasil. #vempraglobo

Seguindo o compromisso de contribuir para um ambiente seguro para nossas pessoas, informamos que ter o esquema completo vacinação contra a Covid-19 é uma condição obrigatória para o trabalho na Globo, presencial ou a distância, e que o comprovante deverá ser apresentado como pré-requisito para a contratação.

Quer saber mais sobre como é trabalhar na Globo? Vem acompanhar nosso dia a dia, desafios e conquistas nas nossas redes:

https://www.linkedin.com/company/globo

https://www.instagram.com/vempraglobo

https://www.youtube.com/c/VemPraGlobo/

Os seus dados pessoais serão utilizados para fins de seleção de candidatos para preenchimento das vagas abertas na Globo.

Os dados pessoais coletados durante o processo seletivo dos candidatos que não forem admitidos neste momento poderão ser mantidos nos bancos de dados para consideração em futuros processos seletivos. Todos os dados coletados serão tratados segundo rígidos padrões de segurança da informação e em total respeito às leis de privacidade aplicáveis, incluindo a Lei 13.709/18, e nos termos de nossa política de privacidade, disponível no link: https://vempraglobo.g.globo/files/politica_de_privacidade.pdf

Ao prosseguir você está ciente e de acordo para realização de sua candidatura nestes termos.

✨somos globo✨

A Globo é feita de gente que quer fazer diferente, fazer junto, fazer o futuro. Gente espalhada por todo o país (e mundo!) trabalhando com conteúdo, notícias, negócios, tecnologia, tudo isso com brasilidade e talento de sobra.

Canais na TV aberta e por assinatura, produtos digitais como Globoplay, Cartola, G1, Ge, Gshow e outros serviços estão reunidos no mesmo lugar.

Na Globo, o encontro de histórias com tecnologia move um time diverso e apaixonado por inovação.

A gente tem a chance de aproximar os brasileiros, criando novas formas de se conectar com eles.

Aqui, cada um faz a transformação acontecer.

Quer fazer parte dessa transformação também?

#VemPraGlobo ;)'

It takes the brightest minds to be a technology leader. It takes imagination to create green energy for the generations to come. At Siemens Gamesa we make real what matters, join our global team.

Position Overview

Conducts analyses of data using various methods and tools to extract information as basis for decision making. Researches, analyzes, consolidates and interprets data using statistical and data analytics methods to create information on business-relevant topics, e.g. market environment, operational process and equipment performance etc. Acquires data from primary or secondary data sources and maintain databases/data systems. Operates and optimizes pre-defined tools, applications and data bases/data management systems. Creates reports and communicates results to various internal and/or external stakeholders (e.g. management, customers).

Relocation will not be offered for this role.

Responsibilities

Support regional Operations team with contractual availability reporting tools and customer inquiries
Provide data analytics on park performance and operational reliability analysis
Perform data analysis, develop insights, and make recommendations to improve operational efficiencies
Provides data analytics based on stakeholder requests and collaboration
Engage with operations and financial management to develop weekly, monthly, and quarterly reports in support of recurring business reviews
Lead consolidation of the current number of reports to produce a more comprehensive analysis that serves a broader spectrum of stakeholders
Evaluates the effectiveness of current digital deliverables, identifies and executes updates and enhancements
Continuous development of industry leading data analysis and procedures to enhance the value of SGRE service
Lead with availability set up as it pertains to new sites
Process data and generate monthly customer reports, weekly health reports, & weekly availability dashboard
Support SQL database maintenance.
Support development of Health Reports for additional turbines platforms
Lead/ Support AM Digital Turbine initiative
Support development, testing, and deployment of field service applications
Contribute to or conduct the maintenance and improvement of internal tools, equipment, processes, and data repositories
Provide end user training in multiple tools to improve reporting accuracy and support process & tool improvements

Required Knowledge, Education, Experience And Skills

Advanced experience with programming language (Python, Shiny, R preferred)
Advanced knowledge of SQL
3-5 years of Wind industry experience
3-5 years of successful experience in database development and report creation
Experience with PowerBI and/or Tableau and/or Minitab or similar
Advanced MS Office (word, power point, excel) skills
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
Be self-motivated, able to think quickly and address problems as they arise
Ability to work in a highly paced environment and demonstrated ability to meet deadlines
Bachelor degree or equivalent experience (Computer Science, Data Science, Engineering, Business Analytics, Mathematics, other).
Team skills and ability to collaboratively work with peers across all levels of the business both local and international
A passion for key performance metrics, using them to communicate status and demonstrate improvements
Qualified applicants must be legally authorized for employment in the United States. Qualified applicants will not require employer sponsored work authorization now or in the future for employment in the United States.
Qualified applicants may be allowed remote working opportunities, based on business needs

Preferred Knowledge/Skills, Education, And Experience

Experience with GRT, WindOne Availability
Knowledge and/or Experience with SCADA systems
Bachelor’s degree in engineering or equivalent degree/experience
Consistently versed in the latest industry cutting edge trends, innovations and applications in the Wind Turbine industry

Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:35:33 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'

2023/06/26 20:35:47 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
The Customer Data Management team is looking for a strong Senior Data Analyst to: Participate in the efforts to improve customer data quality. The Data Analyst will gather disparate data from various data sources; perform analysis on customer information and identify / verify duplicate customer records. Collaborate with customer care, sales operation, account managers, regional data stewards and marketing teams to verify and update customer information. Make necessary updates to customer information via Excel, a custom web application, CRM, and ERP systems. Their duties are, but not limited to, cleansing account data, cleansing mismatch customer hierarchies, and reviewing/ cleansing potential duplicate contacts. The ideal candidate will have a passion to understand, develop, improve, and streamline data through a strong understanding of data management tools and processes.

DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES:

Successfully influence, interact and manage internal and external partners/stakeholders
Will also be responsible for building out initial and ongoing process development, planning & execution
Responsible for maintenance and reporting of performance metrics
Gather, compile, analyze and reconcile data from disparate sources and ensure data integrity across all sources and outputs of data
Define and maintain cross references between data sources to aid in normalizing data to incorporate into centralized repositories
Drive standardization and consistency for all regions
Document data flow, processes and procedures for managing data sources and consolidation
Successfully influence, interact and manage internal and external partners/stakeholders

SKILLS /REQUIREMENTS:

Strong Analytical skills with attention to detail, excellent interpersonal skills and strong teamwork, work ethic and organizational skills
Demonstrate strong experience of data capturing, extraction and analysis expertise
PPI, process, and innovative thinking skills will be valuable for this role
Advanced skills in MS Office Applications, Excel including macros and relational databases
Experience with CRM applications such as Sales Force and Business Intelligence applications such as Cognos and Power BI
Working knowledge of SAP and Oracle JD Edwards Enterprise One (E1) software preferred
Strong communication skills both written and spoken are a requirement
Skilled in establishing and maintaining effective working relationships with team members, but also comfortable working independently
Must be able to develop and maintain documentation to our standards / provide feedback on standards where they can be improved
Create the necessary infrastructure and processes to manage testing/evaluation functions for quality assurance
Experience in project and program management would be an asset

EDUCATION/EXPERIENCE:

High School Diploma or equivalent required
3 - 5 years data analysis'

2023/06/26 20:35:55 - Element found with locator: job-details and  locatorType: id

2023/06/26 20:35:55 - Getting text on element :: 

2023/06/26 20:35:55 - The text is :: 'Sobre a vaga
Want to build a stronger, more sustainable future and cultivate your career? Join Cargill's global team of 160,000 employees who use new technologies, dynamic insights and over 157 years of experience to connect farmers with markets, customers with ingredients, and people and animals with the food they need to thrive.

Job Purpose and Impact

The FSQR Analytics and Reporting Analyst will develop, own and manage a suite of standardized reporting and analytical solutions. In this role, you will partner with business stakeholders and technical teams at the business group, enterprise and global level to deliver moderately complex analytical solutions to address business needs. You will enable the broader organization's focus on insights by maximizing the value of our data and digital core investments.

Key Accountabilities

Gather functional requirements and develop user stories working directly with business stakeholders to enable business insights.
Filter, clean and prepare data to support data reporting and analysis.
Gather requirements, create user stories, resolve solution gaps, architect and model dashboards and build standardized data visualization models to deliver sustainable, effective and efficient reporting and analytical solutions.
Partner with leadership and the team to identify and manage the core set of metrics needed to measure performance.
Evaluate the performance of processes, services and outcomes and drive performance improvement.
Partner with teams to develop a detailed understanding of the business and offer mentorship and technical solutions to solve business problems.
Independently solve moderately complex issues with minimal supervision, while escalating more complex issues to appropriate staff.
Other duties as assigned

Minimum Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalent experience
Advanced/Fluent English
Experience using data visualization applications to develop and deploy insights and reporting

Equal Opportunity Employer, including Disability/Vet.'
